Rating: 4
My husband dreams of this cake... I made one for an office holiday party in December and my coworkers still talk about it. Really, really good. However, there are definitely structural integrity issues, so strategic chilling is key. Melt the white chocolate into the cream at least 24 hours ahead of time so it gets as cold as possible before you finish it, then after you finish the white chocolate cream pop it into the fridge or freezer for at least several hours while the cake cools. Then cool each filled layer in the freezer (we have a big chest freezer) during the assembly process. I have also propped up the cake with straws, then removed them once the white chocolate cream finally set. Also, last time I got lazy and just topped the cake with white chocolate cream and skipped the frosting. Not as dramatic, but honestly just as good.

