Rating: 4
My husband saw this cake on the cover of Bon Appetit and decided that he wanted it for his birthday, so I make it for him. This cake tasted great... everyone loved it. However, it was alot of work. Based on some reviews, I did make a few modifications. The cake stuck in the pans, so I would recommend using parchment paper on the top. I ended up piecing the cake back together as I assembled it, though you couldn't really tell on the final product. For the white chocolate mint cream, I added the specified 1 cup to the white chocolate and chilled it. Then to prevent it from being too runny, I just added 1/2 cup additional whipping cream before I whipped it and put it on the cake. It made enough and I had no problem with it being runny. I also added a little less peppermint extract to the cream. For the peppermint frosting, it took me 40 minutes to get it to a marshmallowy consistency before I took it off the heat and beat it with my hand mixer. That seemed like too much time, but I had no problem with runny frosting, the consistency was fine. The chocolate shavings were necessary for me, because I had alot of cake crumbs in my frosting. We had 9 people eating the cake, and we didn't finish half of it it was so big, but everyone enjoyed it. With all the work, I would only make it again for a special occasion, but really the final product is a great tasting cake.

