So, the cake was great (people were literally gasping BEFORE I cut it). But, a few tips: 1) Use only 1/2 the peppermint like everyone else says. I can't imagine it being twice as pepperminty, given how strong the flavor was. 2) Make Joy of Cooking 7 Minute Frosting instead of this recipe. No point in going through the usual Bon Appetit 5-hour hassle, when something can be done more simply in 1/10th of the time! 2) Keep the darn thing cool. Once you cut your first slice, WATCH OUT!!! The cake starts sliding and moving, and is almost impossible to cut. Truly, the cake was delicious, and my family loved it (made it for Christmas). But, it's a pain, and is not a clean cake once the service starts. Thank God it looks good before, and tastes good after!

